	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Apr 26th 7:49 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.64]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes you can give your pet weapons.&nbsp;&nbsp;Try a gnoll hide lariat sometime ;-) The damage and delay won't make any difference but if the weapon has a proc it will get triggered as part of the normal attack sequence (along with your normal pet proc buffs).  You will not see the graphic, however.  <br><br>Armor given to a pet will work, I have heard, also. but again you will see no graphic.<br><br>Any items given to a pet are gone and cannot be recovered, even if the pet dies, and are lost when the pet despawns (zoning). So, its best not to give nice stuff to your pet.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
