	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 25th 11:36 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.94]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Speaking from a perspective of a character who was well equiped, but not uber-buffed. . . . <br><br>Up until level 9 (when you get magic) I advocate putting points into skills that either help you finish a fight faster (take less damage therefore less down time) or bind-wound better after a fight (less down time).<br><br>The first 5 or so levels I ended up pouring my points into my weapon skill (in my case hand-to-hand).&nbsp;&nbsp;From 6-8 I put my points into bind-wound.  Levels 9 on I typically applied them to the magical skills to reduce that anoying fizzle.<br><br>You would probably want to do something different if you are starting with an HoV and KEI-buffed toon.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Heelem, Froglok Cleric<br>Squwaker, Vah Shir Beastmaster<br>Gilwedar, Woodelf Ranger<br><br>-- The Nameless --</td></tr>
